"In this paper, we address the problem of determining the number of finite field elements with prescribed absolute trace and co-trace for arbitrary characteristic p. We show that this problem can be converted to solving a system of p − 1 linear equations with matrix of coefficients a slight modification of circulant matrix formed by the Kloosterman sums over the field \\(\\mathbb {F}_{p}\\). Also, the asymptotic behavior of this number has been studied utilizing Andre Weil bound on Kloosterman sums over finite fields. The proposed approach is illustrated for characteristic p ≤ 5."
